diagrams.net free?
Yes, diagrams.net (formerly draw.io) is 100% free for personal and commercial use. 
In BookStack, it is a built-in feature that requires zero extra installation. When you edit a page, you can simply click the Drawing icon (a square with a plus sign) to launch the full diagrams.net editor directly inside your browser. 
Key Details for your AI Stack:
No Cost: There are no paid tiers, subscriptions, or feature locks for the standalone web or desktop versions.
Privacy: Since it’s integrated into BookStack, your diagrams are saved as PNG files (with embedded XML data) directly on your own server.
Fully Self-Hostable: While BookStack uses the official diagrams.net server by default, you can actually host your own instance of the diagrams.net editor via Docker and point BookStack to it in your .env file for a completely private, offline setup.
AI Friendly: You can export your diagrams as SVGs or high-res PNGs to include in your public AI project repos on Gitea. 
How to enable it in BookStack:
If it’s not appearing by default in your editor, add this to your BookStack .env file:
bash
# Enable diagrams.net integration
DRAWIO=https://embed.diagrams.net
Use code with caution.

